[Tip 1]
text=_Some buildings (for example, vineyard) have a very small working area, so if building is surrounded with trees and roads, production will stop.
sec=7

[Tip 2]
text=_Watch the fishers hut - after fish resource is exhausted in working area, production will stop.
sec=4

[Tip 3]
text=_Building process will start only after a road is built to the construction site.
sec=4

[Tip 4]
text=_Be sure to send out a geologist to explore site before building a well or mine.
sec=4

[Tip 5]
text=_Your territory can be expanded by building various war buildings - Sentry, Fortress, Baracks, etc.
sec=5

[Tip 6]
text=_Miners will work only if supplied with food.
sec=3

[Tip 7]
text=_Split you roads in several short tracks, trough planting some flags. This will speed up transportation of your wares.
sec=6

[Tip 8]
text=_Always build up some forester- or rangerhut, so you will not go out of trunks and wood.
sec=5

[Tip 9]
text=_Any further questions? Meet us at www.widelands.org. There are our FAQs, the Wiki and of course our Community Forums.
sec=6
